[s1; Special features&]
[s3; Below is the list of TheIDE special features:&]
[s2; Use Ctrl`+Tab to cycle through files. This is perhaps the most 
used key in TheIDE!&]
[s2; Use Alt`+Left to `"return`" to important places (e.g. where 
you have written something). Use Alt`+Right to cycle this places 
forward.&]
[s2; Esc key closes (and reopens) the bottom pane (with compilation 
results etc...)&]
[s2; Rectangular blocks are activated by pressing ALT key.&]
[s2; You can copy files (Ctrl`+C in system file manager, Ctrl`+V 
in TheIDE) into text directly. If more than single file is on 
clipboard, all text is copied.&]
[s2; Dragging file onto TheIDE opens it (as `"temp`" file).&]
[s2; Use Ctrl`+/ to hide project overview `- useful e.g. when editing 
wide layouts.&]
[s2; Use Ctrl`+`-, Ctrl`+`| to split editor vertically/horizontally.]]